##
#Splunk getting started
#

First do not install as root. 

As root now navigate to /opt/splunk/bin issue the following command
Start splunk
- ./splunk start
This will bring up the EULA that you will need to agree to
Then you will be prompted for a UN and PW

You will now go to localhost:8000

- ./splink stop

$ vi ~/.bashrc
 export SPLUNK_HOME="/opt/splunkforwarder"
 export PATH=$PATH:$SPLUNK_HOME/bin 
$ exec bash

Go to /opt/slunkforwarder/bin and do the following 

./splunk start â€”accept-license
./splunk start
./splunk enable boot-start 
./splunk status
